<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">

<%- include('../partials/head', { title: title, description: description, baseUrl: baseUrl, pageType: 'privacy' }) %>

  <body>
    <%- include('../partials/header', { isHome: false, baseUrl: baseUrl, title: title }) %>

      <main>
        <section class="privacy-hero">
          <div class="container">
            <div class="hero-copy">
              <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
              <p class="lead">Learn how CollectIn protects your privacy and handles your data.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="privacy-content">
          <div class="container">
            <div class="privacy-text">
              <p class="last-updated"><strong>Last updated:</strong> September 2025</p>

              <article>
                <h2>Overview</h2>
                <p>CollectIn is a browser extension that helps you organize your LinkedIn saved posts into collections.
                  We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about how our extension works.</p>
                <p><strong>The short version:</strong> CollectIn stores all your data locally in your browser and never
                  sends any information to external servers.</p>
              </article>

              <article>
                <h2>Information We Collect and Store</h2>
                <h3>Local Browser Storage Only</h3>
                <p>CollectIn stores the following information locally in your browser's storage:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Collection names:</strong> The names you give to your post collections</li>
                  <li><strong>Post assignments:</strong> Which posts belong to which collections</li>
                  <li><strong>Extension preferences:</strong> Your settings and preferences for how the extension
                    behaves</li>
                </ul>
                <p>This data is stored using your browser's local storage mechanisms and never leaves your device.</p>

                <h3>Information We Do NOT Collect</h3>
                <p>CollectIn does not collect, access, store, or transmit:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Your LinkedIn login credentials or authentication tokens</li>
                  <li>The content of your LinkedIn posts or messages</li>
                  <li>Your LinkedIn profile information</li>
                  <li>Your browsing history outside of LinkedIn</li>
                  <li>Any personally identifiable information</li>
                  <li>Analytics or usage data</li>
                </ul>
              </article>

              <article>
                <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
                <p>The information stored locally by CollectIn is used solely to:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Display your collections in LinkedIn's saved posts interface</li>
                  <li>Remember which posts belong to which collections</li>
                  <li>Provide filtering functionality based on your collections</li>
                  <li>Maintain your extension preferences</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Since all data is stored locally, we have no access to your information and cannot use it for any
                  other purposes.</p>
              </article>

              <article>
                <h2>Data Sharing and Third Parties</h2>
                <p>CollectIn does not share any data with third parties because:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>All data is stored locally in your browser</li>
                  <li>No data is transmitted to our servers or any external services</li>
                  <li>We do not have access to your data</li>
                  <li>We do not use analytics services or tracking</li>
                </ul>
              </article>

              <article>
                <h2>LinkedIn Integration</h2>
                <p>CollectIn operates by:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Reading the DOM:</strong> The extension reads LinkedIn's webpage structure to identify
                    saved posts and add collection features</li>
                  <li><strong>Modifying the interface:</strong> Adding collection badges, filters, and management tools
                    to LinkedIn's existing interface</li>
                  <li><strong>No API calls:</strong> We do not make any calls to LinkedIn's API or any external APIs
                  </li>
                  <li><strong>No account access:</strong> We never access your LinkedIn account, authentication, or
                    perform actions on your behalf</li>
                </ul>
                <p>The extension only enhances the visual presentation of LinkedIn's saved posts page and does not
                  interact with LinkedIn's servers.</p>
              </article>

              <article>
                <h2>Data Security</h2>
                <p>Since all data is stored locally in your browser:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Your data is protected by your browser's security mechanisms</li>
                  <li>Data is not transmitted over the internet</li>
                  <li>No risk of server breaches or external data theft</li>
                  <li>You maintain complete control over your data</li>
                </ul>
              </article>

              <article>
                <h2>Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
                <p>Your collection data is retained locally until:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>You uninstall the CollectIn extension</li>
                  <li>You clear your browser's local storage/data</li>
                  <li>You manually delete collections within the extension</li>
                </ul>
                <p>If you uninstall CollectIn, all associated data will be removed from your browser. Your LinkedIn
                  saved posts will remain unchanged in your LinkedIn account.</p>
              </article>

              <article>
                <h2>Browser Permissions</h2>
                <p>CollectIn requires minimal browser permissions:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Access to linkedin.com:</strong> To modify the saved posts page interface</li>
                  <li><strong>Storage permission:</strong> To save your collections locally in your browser</li>
                </ul>
                <p>We do not request permissions for:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Access to other websites</li>
                  <li>Reading your browsing history</li>
                  <li>Accessing your downloads or files</li>
                  <li>Managing your apps, extensions, or themes</li>
                </ul>
              </article>

              <article>
                <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
                <p>CollectIn is not intended for use by children under 13 years of age. Since we do not collect any
                  personal information, we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.</p>
              </article>

              <article>
                <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
                <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Update the "Last updated" date at the top of this policy</li>
                  <li>Post the new Privacy Policy on this page</li>
                  <li>For significant changes, provide notice through the extension or our website</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Your continued use of CollectIn after any changes indicates your acceptance of the updated Privacy
                  Policy.</p>
              </article>

              <article>
                <h2>Contact Information</h2>
                <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or CollectIn's privacy practices, you can contact
                  us:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Through the Chrome Web Store listing</li>
                  <li>By visiting our help documentation</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Since CollectIn operates entirely locally and we don't collect personal data, most privacy-related
                  questions can be answered by this policy.</p>
              </article>

              <article>
                <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
                <p>CollectIn is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by LinkedIn Corporation. LinkedIn is a
                  trademark of LinkedIn Corporation.</p>
              </article>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </main>

      <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
  </body>

</html>